{"article_id":"swcJnpYdrDT3IFNb","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"The Republican race for the presidential nomination is down to just one man and one number :","depth":7},{"id":1,"text":"Donald Trump and 1,237","depth":8},{"id":2,"text":"- the number of delegates","depth":9},{"id":3,"text":"required","depth":10},{"id":4,"text":"to clinch the nomination .","depth":10},{"id":5,"text":"Can Trump win 1,237 delegates by the end of the primary season on June 7 ?","depth":7},{"id":6,"text":"Will he be forced to plunder among the more than 100 unbound or currently uncommitted delegates","depth":9},{"id":7,"text":"who will make the trip to Cleveland","depth":10},{"id":8,"text":"in order to win on a first ballot at the Republican National Convention ?","depth":10},{"id":9,"text":"Or are we all but assured of a multi-ballot convention ?","depth":8},{"id":10,"text":"Any pundit","depth":9},{"id":11,"text":"giving confident answers to these questions","depth":9},{"id":12,"text":"is full of it ,","depth":8},{"id":13,"text":"so surveyed some of the best delegate obsessives and political experts","depth":9},{"id":14,"text":"we know","depth":9},{"id":15,"text":"on how many delegates they expect Trump to win in the remaining contests .","depth":8},{"id":16,"text":"Trump has 695 delegates now ,","depth":9},{"id":17,"text":"and , on average , our respondents estimate","depth":13},{"id":18,"text":"he will still be just a little bit short of 1,237 on June 7 ,","depth":14},{"id":19,"text":"when California wraps up the primary calendar .","depth":14},{"id":20,"text":"He might be close enough , though ,","depth":13},{"id":21,"text":"that he could clinch the nomination in the six weeks between California and Cleveland .","depth":13},{"id":22,"text":"If that ' s the baseline case , however ,","depth":12},{"id":23,"text":"it wouldn ' t take much for Trump to deviate from it in either direction .","depth":12},{"id":24,"text":"Outperform these estimates in California , for instance ,","depth":12},{"id":25,"text":"and Trump could reach or surpass 1,237 delegates on June 7 .","depth":12},{"id":26,"text":"Lose a winner-take-all or winner-take-most state","depth":14},{"id":27,"text":"where these estimates have him favored ,","depth":14},{"id":28,"text":"however ,","depth":13},{"id":29,"text":"and Trump could be well short of a majority .","depth":12},{"id":30,"text":"There are few truly proportional states left on the GOP ' s primary calendar ,","depth":10},{"id":31,"text":"so small shifts in any state can have major consequences in the delegate count .","depth":10},{"id":32,"text":"That ' s why we surveyed this group .","depth":9},{"id":33,"text":"My own personal delegate projection took a beating Tuesday","depth":8},{"id":34,"text":"because I thought","depth":9},{"id":35,"text":"Ted Cruz would win Missouri by a small amount","depth":10},{"id":36,"text":"instead of losing it by a small amount .","depth":10},{"id":37,"text":"In addition to Nate Silver ' s and my estimates , we tried to include a diverse set of opinions from across the political spectrum .","depth":8},{"id":38,"text":"We also focused on analysts","depth":9},{"id":39,"text":"who have been following the delegate race closely","depth":10},{"id":40,"text":"and know the intricacies of the GOP ' s delegate rules .","depth":10},{"id":41,"text":"Our panel included these people :","depth":7},{"id":42,"text":"Adam Geller :","depth":8},{"id":43,"text":"founder and CEO of National Research Inc. and the lead pollster for Chris Christie ' s presidential campaign","depth":8},{"id":44,"text":"Daniel Nichanian :","depth":9},{"id":45,"text":"contributing editor to Daily Kos Elections and PhD candidate in political science at the University of Chicago .","depth":9},{"id":46,"text":"Henry Olsen :","depth":10},{"id":47,"text":"senior fellow at the Ethics and Public Policy Center","depth":10},{"id":48,"text":"Patrick Ruffini :","depth":11},{"id":49,"text":"co-founder and partner at Echelon Insights and chairman and founder of Engage","depth":11},{"id":50,"text":"David Wasserman :","depth":11},{"id":51,"text":"House editor at the Cook Political Report and contributor","depth":11},{"id":52,"text":"To best reflect the group consensus ,","depth":8},{"id":53,"text":"we used an \" olympic average \"","depth":9},{"id":54,"text":"in which we discarded the highest and lowest estimates in each state","depth":10},{"id":55,"text":"and averaged the remainder .","depth":10},{"id":56,"text":"Because of this averaging process","depth":11},{"id":57,"text":"- and because we told panelists","depth":12},{"id":58,"text":"they could list probabilistic forecasts instead of deterministic ones -","depth":12},{"id":59,"text":"in some cases the average reflects a number of delegates","depth":11},{"id":60,"text":"that it would be mathematically impossible for Trump to achieve .","depth":11},{"id":61,"text":"For instance , our average has Trump with 15 delegates in winner-take-all Delaware ,","depth":11},{"id":62,"text":"which has 16 delegates at stake .","depth":11},{"id":63,"text":"This is equivalent to saying","depth":12},{"id":64,"text":"that Trump is highly likely but not quite certain to win Delaware ,","depth":12},{"id":65,"text":"according to the panel .","depth":11},{"id":66,"text":"Overall , our average response suggests","depth":10},{"id":67,"text":"that Trump will win 513 delegates the rest of the way .","depth":10},{"id":68,"text":"When combined with the 695","depth":11},{"id":69,"text":"he ' s won so far ,","depth":11},{"id":70,"text":"that means he ' d fall 29 delegates short of the 1,237","depth":11},{"id":71,"text":"needed","depth":12},{"id":72,"text":"to win on the first ballot .","depth":12},{"id":73,"text":"Here is the olympic average for each upcoming contest","depth":7},{"id":74,"text":"( we ' ve left out some contests with only unbound delegates ;","depth":8},{"id":75,"text":"see the footnotes for more detail ) :","depth":8},{"id":76,"text":"DELEGATES DATE CONTEST AVAILABLE","depth":5},{"id":77,"text":"PROJECTED FOR TRUMP","depth":5},{"id":78,"text":"3/22 Arizona 58 58 Utah 40 4","depth":5},{"id":79,"text":"American Samoa 9 2 4/5 Wisconsin 42 25","depth":6},{"id":80,"text":"4/9 Colorado 34 7 4/16 Wyoming","depth":7},{"id":81,"text":"14 1 4/19 New York","depth":8},{"id":82,"text":"95 71 4/26 Maryland","depth":9},{"id":83,"text":"38 31 Connecticut","depth":10},{"id":84,"text":"28 19 Rhode Island","depth":11},{"id":85,"text":"19 10 Pennsylvania","depth":13},{"id":86,"text":"17 16 Delaware 16 15 5/3 Indiana","depth":13},{"id":87,"text":"57 37 5/10 Nebraska","depth":13},{"id":88,"text":"36 1 West Virginia","depth":14},{"id":89,"text":"34 33 5/17 Oregon","depth":15},{"id":90,"text":"28 12 5/24 Washington","depth":16},{"id":91,"text":"44 17 6/7 California 172 93 New Jersey 51 51 South Dakota","depth":17},{"id":92,"text":"29 0 Montana","depth":18},{"id":93,"text":"27 0 New Mexico 24 10","depth":18},{"id":94,"text":"New Trump delegates 513","depth":5},{"id":95,"text":"Delegates to date 695","depth":5},{"id":96,"text":"Total 1,208","depth":4},{"id":97,"text":"How many more delegates will Donald Trump win ?","depth":5},{"id":98,"text":"Trump projections","depth":7},{"id":99,"text":"based on an olympic average of estimates from Nate Silver , Harry Enten , Adam Geller","depth":9},{"id":100,"text":"( National Research Inc. ) ,","depth":9},{"id":101,"text":"Daniel Nichanian","depth":10},{"id":102,"text":"( Daily Kos ) ,","depth":10},{"id":103,"text":"Henry Olsen","depth":11},{"id":104,"text":"( Ethics and Public Policy Center ) ,","depth":11},{"id":105,"text":"Margie Omero","depth":11},{"id":106,"text":"( Purple Insights ) , Patrick","depth":11},{"id":107,"text":"If Trump does , in fact , get 1,208 delegates ,","depth":9},{"id":108,"text":"he still might win on a first ballot .","depth":9},{"id":109,"text":"He would need only a fraction of the delegates","depth":11},{"id":110,"text":"that are currently unbound","depth":12},{"id":111,"text":"( or will be unbound )","depth":12},{"id":112,"text":"to reach 1,237 .","depth":10},{"id":113,"text":"Who exactly are these unbound or uncommitted delegates ?","depth":10},{"id":114,"text":"Some , like the six from the Virgin Islands , were elected by voters","depth":13},{"id":115,"text":"to be \" uncommitted , \"","depth":13},{"id":116,"text":"but they may commit to a candidate closer to the convention .","depth":12},{"id":117,"text":"Others , like the 54 Pennsylvania district delegates , are automatically unbound","depth":14},{"id":118,"text":"and have been elected as unbound for decades","depth":15},{"id":119,"text":"( see :","depth":16},{"id":120,"text":"when Gerald Ford beat Ronald Reagan in the 1976 primary ) .","depth":16},{"id":121,"text":"These delegates are free to choose whichever candidate they want on all ballots .","depth":13},{"id":122,"text":"In addition , some delegates from candidates","depth":15},{"id":123,"text":"who have withdrawn from the race","depth":15},{"id":124,"text":"may become available to Trump ,","depth":14},{"id":125,"text":"depending on the state ' s rules .","depth":13},{"id":126,"text":"Although it ' s hard to know Trump ' s exact chance","depth":9},{"id":127,"text":"of getting 29 delegates from this group ,","depth":9},{"id":128,"text":"Trump probably would have a decent shot","depth":9},{"id":129,"text":"at reaching 1,237 .","depth":9},{"id":130,"text":"All of the respondents agree","depth":8},{"id":131,"text":"that Trump is not likely to get close to 1,237 delegates before June 7 ,","depth":11},{"id":132,"text":"when California and four other states vote .","depth":11},{"id":133,"text":"The closest","depth":12},{"id":134,"text":"Trump came","depth":12},{"id":135,"text":"was 1,088 delegates .","depth":11},{"id":136,"text":"And even the most optimistic Trump projection has him hitting 1,244","depth":10},{"id":137,"text":"after all the states have voted .","depth":10},{"id":138,"text":"That leaves Trump with very little room for error","depth":8},{"id":139,"text":"to reach a majority of delegates","depth":9},{"id":140,"text":"without at least some of the currently unpledged or uncommitted delegates coming to his aid .","depth":9},{"id":141,"text":"Part of the reason","depth":9},{"id":142,"text":"we ' ll have to wait so long","depth":9},{"id":143,"text":"is how the rest of the calendar breaks down .","depth":8},{"id":144,"text":"The month of April ,","depth":10},{"id":145,"text":"which includes a lot of primaries in the Northeast ,","depth":10},{"id":146,"text":"should be good for Trump .","depth":9},{"id":147,"text":"May has far fewer contests ,","depth":9},{"id":148,"text":"and Trump is expected to do poorly in Nebraska , Oregon and Washington .","depth":9},{"id":149,"text":"Not surprisingly , our respondents ' estimates differed greatly in a number of states .","depth":8},{"id":150,"text":"If you ' re looking for the states","depth":11},{"id":151,"text":"that could be make-or-break for Trump ,","depth":11},{"id":152,"text":"then look to Wisconsin , New York , Indiana and California .","depth":10},{"id":153,"text":"In all four , Trump ' s expected number of delegates won differed by at least 36 among the respondents .","depth":9},{"id":154,"text":"Wisconsin","depth":10},{"id":155,"text":"( April 5 ) :","depth":12},{"id":156,"text":"Forty-two delegates are at stake ,","depth":13},{"id":157,"text":"and it ' s winner-take-all on the congressional district and state level .","depth":13},{"id":158,"text":"Trump led in the most recent poll , but with only 30 percent ,","depth":12},{"id":159,"text":"and he had a very high unfavorable rating .","depth":12},{"id":160,"text":"( April 5 ) :","depth":11},{"id":161,"text":"Forty-two delegates are at stake ,","depth":12},{"id":162,"text":"and it ' s winner-take-all on the congressional district and state level .","depth":12},{"id":163,"text":"Trump led in the most recent poll , but with only 30 percent ,","depth":11},{"id":164,"text":"and he had a very high unfavorable rating .","depth":11},{"id":165,"text":"New York","depth":11},{"id":166,"text":"( April 19 ) :","depth":11},{"id":167,"text":"All of our respondents had Trump winning a majority of the state ' s 95 delegates ,","depth":12},{"id":168,"text":"but some believe","depth":13},{"id":169,"text":"the other candidates can cut into Trump ' s edge","depth":14},{"id":170,"text":"by keeping him under 50 percent in a number of congressional districts or statewide .","depth":14},{"id":171,"text":"If Trump wins more than 50 percent in a district or statewide ,","depth":12},{"id":172,"text":"he wins all delegates in that district or statewide .","depth":12},{"id":173,"text":"( April 19 ) :","depth":10},{"id":174,"text":"All of our respondents had","depth":13},{"id":175,"text":"Trump winning a majority of the state ' s 95 delegates ,","depth":13},{"id":176,"text":"but some believe","depth":13},{"id":177,"text":"the other candidates can cut into Trump ' s edge","depth":14},{"id":178,"text":"by keeping him under 50 percent in a number of congressional districts or statewide .","depth":14},{"id":179,"text":"If Trump wins more than 50 percent in a district or statewide ,","depth":12},{"id":180,"text":"he wins all delegates in that district or statewide .","depth":12},{"id":181,"text":"Indiana","depth":8},{"id":182,"text":"( May 3 ) :","depth":10},{"id":183,"text":"It ' s hard to say to whom Indiana ' s 57 delegates will go","depth":11},{"id":184,"text":"because there hasn ' t really been any polling there ,","depth":12},{"id":185,"text":"and the Hoosier State doesn ' t line up well demographically with any other Midwestern state .","depth":12},{"id":186,"text":"( May 3 ) :","depth":10},{"id":187,"text":"It ' s hard to say to whom Indiana ' s 57 delegates will go","depth":11},{"id":188,"text":"because there hasn ' t really been any polling there ,","depth":12},{"id":189,"text":"and the Hoosier State doesn ' t line up well demographically with any other Midwestern state .","depth":12},{"id":190,"text":"California","depth":13},{"id":191,"text":"( June 7 ) :","depth":13},{"id":192,"text":"The biggest prize of all , California will award 172 delegates","depth":14},{"id":193,"text":"- 159 by congressional district and 13 to the winner statewide .","depth":14},{"id":194,"text":"No one knows","depth":14},{"id":195,"text":"how the very Democratic districts","depth":16},{"id":196,"text":"( and hence those with very few Republican voters )","depth":16},{"id":197,"text":"around Los Angeles or San Francisco will vote .","depth":15},{"id":198,"text":"The average statewide poll shows Trump ahead , but again with only 30 percent .","depth":11},{"id":199,"text":"Indeed , there was a somewhat bimodal distribution in the total number of delegates","depth":12},{"id":200,"text":"our respondents expected Trump to reach .","depth":12},{"id":201,"text":"Three of us have Trump earning from 1,136 to 1,156 ,","depth":13},{"id":202,"text":"and three have him winning from 1,237 to 1,244 .","depth":13},{"id":203,"text":"( The other two respondents have him in the 1200s but short of 1,237 . )","depth":12},{"id":204,"text":"That may be why you read some pieces","depth":12},{"id":205,"text":"that seem to indicate","depth":13},{"id":206,"text":"that Trump is well on his way to winning on the first ballot ,","depth":13},{"id":207,"text":"but other people seem to think","depth":12},{"id":208,"text":"there ' s very little chance of it .","depth":12},{"id":209,"text":"Smart people disagree .","depth":12},{"id":210,"text":"And a single upset in a winner-take-all state could change the map significantly .","depth":12},{"id":211,"text":"Our panel has Trump winning all 58 delegates in winner-take-all Arizona , for instance ,","depth":13},{"id":212,"text":"which votes Tuesday .","depth":13},{"id":213,"text":"If he lost there ,","depth":13},{"id":214,"text":"it could make it very hard to get to 1,237 .","depth":13},{"id":215,"text":"Perhaps what becomes clearest is that there is still a lot","depth":11},{"id":216,"text":"we don ' t know .","depth":11},{"id":217,"text":"We ' ll have to watch","depth":11},{"id":218,"text":"and see","depth":12},{"id":219,"text":"if there are any clues in the voting over the next month .","depth":12},{"id":220,"text":"For now , hang on for a wild ride .","depth":9},{"id":221,"text":"Listen to the latest episode of the politics podcast .","depth":1}],"relations":[{"parent":443,"left":442,"right":221,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":442,"left":315,"right":441,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":315,"left":297,"right":314,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":297,"left":258,"right":296,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":258,"left":231,"right":257,"relation":"topic","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":231,"left":226,"right":230,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":226,"left":0,"right":225,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":225,"left":1,"right":224,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":224,"left":2,"right":223,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":223,"left":3,"right":4,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":230,"left":5,"right":229,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":229,"left":228,"right":9,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":228,"left":6,"right":227,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":227,"left":7,"right":8,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":257,"left":236,"right":256,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":236,"left":233,"right":235,"relation":"explanation","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":233,"left":232,"right":12,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":232,"left":10,"right":11,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":235,"left":234,"right":15,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":234,"left":13,"right":14,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":256,"left":252,"right":255,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":252,"left":249,"right":251,"relation":"evaluation","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":249,"left":16,"right":248,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":248,"left":242,"right":247,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":242,"left":240,"right":241,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":240,"left":238,"right":239,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":238,"left":17,"right":237,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":237,"left":18,"right":19,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":239,"left":20,"right":21,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":241,"left":22,"right":23,"relation":"condition","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":247,"left":243,"right":246,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":243,"left":24,"right":25,"relation":"condition","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":246,"left":245,"right":29,"relation":"condition","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":245,"left":244,"right":28,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":244,"left":26,"right":27,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":251,"left":250,"right":32,"relation":"explanation","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":250,"left":30,"right":31,"relation":"causal","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":255,"left":33,"right":254,"relation":"explanation","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":254,"left":34,"right":253,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":253,"left":35,"right":36,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":296,"left":272,"right":295,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":272,"left":262,"right":271,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":262,"left":261,"right":41,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":261,"left":37,"right":260,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":260,"left":38,"right":259,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":259,"left":39,"right":40,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":271,"left":263,"ri